<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 02 at 8:03PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Bibb,
southeastern Monroe, northeastern Crawford and southwestern Jones
Counties through 830 PM EDT...
At 803 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Lake Tobesofkee, or 9
miles northwest of Macon, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Macon, Payne, Payne City, Wesleyan, Lizella, Lake Tobesofkee,
Bolingbroke, Arkwright and Dames Ferry.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
